Text.Value: We are just leaving. We have a celebration to attend.
What's a Black Mass?
We should go, brother. The master must be told.
I don't know. I don't normally accept invitations from strangers.
Sure, I'll see you there.
You must excuse my sister, she's a terrible bore.
Please, pay my brother no mind. His imagination - and his mouth - get the better of him sometimes.
You don't know what my lord is capable of. You don't know his power.
Hello beautiful, I didn't see you there.
There is no time, we are expected back at the palace.
I look forward to seeing you at the palace, though. It'll be a once-in-a-lifetime experience, I promise.
He's close. I'll see him at camp tonight.
I'd like to see him try, the little worm.
It's not for the master, it's for me. I want a beating heart there, ready for me when the Mass is complete and we're finally granted our freedom.
Listen in.
As if you know anything about it.
Yeah, let's go deliver the good news.
Where is he? Tell us!
A terrible pity, but if you find yourself in the Lower City, you're most certainly invited.
I'll skip the Black Mass. You will too if you know what's good for you.
Somewhere you and your master will never find him.
I didn't realise we had company.
Anyone dumb enough to get lured away by you two deserves whatever they get.
The Black Mass has been two centuries in the making. We can take five minutes to find one more person.
Are you ready to go now, brother? Have you been rejected enough?
I'd be game, if you're looking for volunteers.
Great! The palace looks out over the Lower City, you won't be able to miss it.
This is not the time, Petras.
One more mark, then we can go.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Gwen Lee] Animation of Dalyria seducing the player.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: player is a little far away from the two vampire spawn

Text.Value: You should come! It'll be the talk of Baldur's Gate.
But it does not matter, we were just leaving anyway. Weren't we, Petras?
Thank goodness we're such good friends, then!
After two hundred years of rats, I think we deserve a real drink.
We were just discussing a ... celebration being held in the palace of Cazador Szarr.

EditorData.NodeContext: pause before 'celebration'. The event is actually a blood ritual, but they don't want to tell guests that.

Text.Value: What are you talking about?
So it seems. I just need a minute, then we can go.
Come brother, we have wasted enough time.
'Mark'? That doesn't sound good.
Fine. But this isn't over - we'll see you again.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Both vampire spawn turn to mist and vanish, leaving just Astarion and the party in the room

EditorData.VFXTags: [WI][Cine] Can sync up with the VFX for the mist/vanishing act done on WYR_VampireSpawns_OM_Astarion_COM

Text.Value: Black Mass? Is that the Ritual of Profane Ascension?
You know Astarion?
What did you say?
Forgive us for not escorting you there, but my brother and I must attend to another matter first.
But you look like someone who enjoys a party. There's a celebration being held in the palace of Cazador Szarr - why not join us?
No need to go looking - he'll find you soon enough.
I'll pass. Doesn't sound like my thing.
This is not the time, brother. The master must be told.
Listen in.
And what do I get if I tell you?
Yes, of course, dear sister. I just need a moment and then we can leave.
Well hello, beautiful! Aren't you a sight to behold?
You must excuse my brother, he forgets that we have a very pressing engagement.
Wait - you know Astarion?
Yes, dear sister, I know we have places to be. We'll leave once our good friends here have departed.
The master said we have enough - the Black Mass is ready to begin.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Gwen Lee] Continuation of Dalyria seducing the player, but Petra stops her.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: player hides just out of view

Text.Value: Of course not, we were merely discussing a... celebration to be held in the palace of Cazador Szarr.
How about we leave your blood inside your body?
Relax, the Black Mass won't start until master drags Astarion from whatever hole he's hiding in. We have time to find one more person.

Synopsis:
Dalyria and Petra at the flophouse.
They are looking for Astarion at the place where they used to "hunt".
This is a dialog for when they meet the player without Astarion.
Dalyria tries to seduce the player and invite them to Cazador's mansion, but Petra tells her not to get distracted - they are only here to look for "that person".
